properties.description: Performs postal and national address search, street search, suburb search.

headers.name: ApplicationID
headers.description: Send System APP ID – All interaction from source system should have same Application ID.

headers.name: TransactionContextID
headers.description: Supply GUID – It is generated once at the initiation point of the transaction and is propagated throughout the transaction lifecycle through the service execution.

headers.name: Version
headers.description: Version of the API to be called. Use the value specified in example (highest version)

headers.name: MessageTraceID
headers.description: This element is a unique identifier associated with each message. Response and Fault messages should have a distinct MessageTraceID from request messages. Element can be used to achieve idempotent behaviour on server side.

properties.value:
<!--
    IMPORTANT:
    - Policy elements can appear only within the <inbound>, <outbound>, <backend> section elements.
    - To apply a policy to the incoming request (before it is forwarded to the backend service), place a corresponding policy element within the <inbound> section element.
    - To apply a policy to the outgoing response (before it is sent back to the caller), place a corresponding policy element within the <outbound> section element.
    - To add a policy, place the cursor at the desired insertion point and select a policy from the sidebar.
    - To remove a policy, delete the corresponding policy statement from the policy document.
    - Position the <base> element within a section element to inherit all policies from the corresponding section element in the enclosing scope.
    - Remove the <base> element to prevent inheriting policies from the corresponding section element in the enclosing scope.
    - Policies are applied in the order of their appearance, from the top down.
    - Comments within policy elements are not supported and may disappear. Place your comments between policy elements or at a higher level scope.
-->
<policies>
	<inbound>
		<base />
	</inbound>
	<backend>
		<base />
	</backend>
	<outbound>
		<base />
		<choose>
			<when condition="@(context.Response.StatusCode == 200)">
				<set-body>@{
                    JObject o = context.Response.Body.As<JObject>(preserveContent: true);
                    var items = o.SelectTokens("$.hits.._source");
                    if (items != null)
                    {
                        byte[] IV = Convert.FromBase64String("{{api-encryptiv}}");
                        byte[] key = Convert.FromBase64String("{{api-encryptkey}}");
                        string encryptExcpetions = "{{encrypt-exception-values}}";
                        string[] arrEncryptExceptions = encryptExcpetions.Split(',');

                        foreach (JToken item in items)
                        {
                            JToken propertyNumber = item["propertyNumber"];
                            if (propertyNumber != null)
                            {
                                if (propertyNumber.ToString().Trim().Length > 0)
                                {
                                    bool toEncrypt = (Array.Exists(arrEncryptExceptions, e => e.Trim() == propertyNumber.ToString().Trim())) ? false : true;
                                    if (toEncrypt)
                                    {
                                        string propertyNumberValue = propertyNumber.ToString();
                                        byte[] responseByte = Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(propertyNumberValue);                                    
                                        byte[] encryptedBytes = responseByte.Encrypt("Aes", key, IV);
                                        string encryptedvalue = Convert.ToBase64String(encryptedBytes);
                                        string encodedurlvalue =  System.Net.WebUtility.UrlEncode(encryptedvalue);
                                        item["propertyNumber"] = encodedurlvalue;
                                    }
                                }
                            }
                            JToken parentPropertyNumber = item["parentPropertyNumber"];
                            if (parentPropertyNumber != null)
                            {
                                if (parentPropertyNumber.ToString().Trim().Length > 0)
                                {
                                    bool toEncrypt = (Array.Exists(arrEncryptExceptions, e => e.Trim() == parentPropertyNumber.ToString().Trim())) ? false : true;
                                    if (toEncrypt)
                                    {
                                        string parentPropertyNumberValue = parentPropertyNumber.ToString();
                                        byte[] responseByte = Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(parentPropertyNumberValue);
                                        byte[] encryptedBytes = responseByte.Encrypt("Aes", key, IV);
                                        string encryptedvalue = Convert.ToBase64String(encryptedBytes);
                                        string encodedurlvalue =  System.Net.WebUtility.UrlEncode(encryptedvalue);
                                        item["parentPropertyNumber"] = encodedurlvalue;
                                    }                                    
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    }
                    return o.ToString();                
                }</set-body>
			</when>
		</choose>
	</outbound>
	<on-error>
		<base />
	</on-error>
</policies>

<!--
    IMPORTANT:
    - Policy elements can appear only within the <inbound>, <outbound>, <backend> section elements.
    - To apply a policy to the incoming request (before it is forwarded to the backend service), place a corresponding policy element within the <inbound> section element.
    - To apply a policy to the outgoing response (before it is sent back to the caller), place a corresponding policy element within the <outbound> section element.
    - To add a policy, place the cursor at the desired insertion point and select a policy from the sidebar.
    - To remove a policy, delete the corresponding policy statement from the policy document.
    - Position the <base> element within a section element to inherit all policies from the corresponding section element in the enclosing scope.
    - Remove the <base> element to prevent inheriting policies from the corresponding section element in the enclosing scope.
    - Policies are applied in the order of their appearance, from the top down.
    - Comments within policy elements are not supported and may disappear. Place your comments between policy elements or at a higher level scope.
-->
<policies>
	<inbound>
		<base />
		<authentication-basic username="{{api-authentication-username}}" password="{{api-authentication-password}}" />
	</inbound>
	<backend>
		<base />
	</backend>
	<outbound>
		<base />
	</outbound>
	<on-error>
		<base />
	</on-error>
</policies>
